#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:377
msgid ""
"Settlers are one of the key units in the game, as they are your main means "
"of founding new cities, and can also improve terrain; see the help on "
"Terrain and Terrain Alterations."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:381 data/classic/units.ruleset:483
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:495
msgid ""
"Upkeep for Settlers is in food as well as production, and a Settler can die "
"if its supporting city runs out of food. Settlers in a Republic or Democracy "
"require twice as much food per turn."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:388
msgid "Militia"
msgstr "Опълченци"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:414 data/civ2/units.ruleset:464
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:669 data/classic/units.ruleset:607
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:629 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:608
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:761 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:673
msgid ""
"This unit may be built from the start of the game. It is the weakest "
"offensive unit."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:420 data/civ2/units.ruleset:470
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:675 data/classic/units.ruleset:613
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:635 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:614
