#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:724 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:703
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:768
msgid ""
"Legions are heavily armed and well disciplined infantry units with an "
"excellent offensive value."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:483 data/civ2/units.ruleset:601
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:802 data/classic/units.ruleset:745
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:767 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:746
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:898 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:806
msgid "Musketeers"
msgstr "Мускетари"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:510
msgid ""
"Musketeers are infantry equipped with early firearms and replace Phalanx as "
"the preferred city defender."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:517 data/civ2/units.ruleset:742
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:836 data/classic/units.ruleset:851
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:873 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:887
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:932 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:840
msgid "Riflemen"
msgstr "Пехотинци"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:543 data/civ2/units.ruleset:768
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:866
msgid ""
"Riflemen are World War-era infantry, very good at defending your cities."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:549 data/civ2/units.ruleset:842
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1054 data/classic/units.ruleset:951
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:973 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:987
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1197 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1058
msgid "Mech. Inf."
msgstr "Механизирана пехота"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:575
msgid ""
"Mechanized Infantry has the strongest defense strength of any land unit, but "
"is only available near the end of the technology tree."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:582 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1068
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1285 data/classic/units.ruleset:1113
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1136 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1213
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1431 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1289
msgid "Cavalry"
msgstr "Кавалерия"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:608
msgid ""
"Cavalry are mounted warriors and an early shock-troop that can penetrate "
"deep into enemy territory."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:615 data/civ2/units.ruleset:908
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1122 data/classic/units.ruleset:1017
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1040 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1053
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1265 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1126
msgid "Chariot"
msgstr "Колесница"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:641
msgid ""
"Chariots are horse-pulled war wagons, stronger but more expensive than "
"Cavalry."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:647 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1004
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1222 data/classic/units.ruleset:1049
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1072 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1149
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1368 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1226
msgid "Knights"
msgstr "Рицари"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:674 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1031
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1249 data/classic/units.ruleset:1076
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1099 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1176
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1395 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1253
msgid "Knights are mounted and heavily armored warriors."
msgstr "Рицарите са тежко бронирани войни на коне."

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:679 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1099
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1316 data/classic/units.ruleset:1144
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1167 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1244
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1462 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1320
msgid "Armor"
msgstr "Бронетанкови"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:705 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1125
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1170 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1193
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1270
msgid ""
"Armors are motorized war wagons that are faster, stronger, and can take more "
"damage than any mounted unit."
msgstr ""
"Бронетанковите части са моторизирани бойни коли, които са по-бързи, по-силни "
"и могат да поемат повече щети от всяка кавалерийска единица."

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:712 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1132
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1351 data/classic/units.ruleset:1177
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1200 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1277
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1497 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1355
msgid "Catapult"
msgstr "Катапулт"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:738 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1158
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1377 data/classic/units.ruleset:1203
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1226 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1303
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1381
msgid ""
"Catapults are large rock-throwing machines of war. They are very strong "
"attackers but equally weak defenders and will need an escort to be effective."
msgstr ""
"Катапултите са големи каменометни обсадни машини. Много са силни в атака, но "
"са също толкова слаби при защита и се нуждаят от ескорт, за да бъдат "
"ефективни."

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:745 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1165
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1389 data/classic/units.ruleset:1210
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1233 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1310
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1538 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1393
msgid "Cannon"
msgstr "Топ"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:771 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1191
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1236 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1259
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1336
msgid ""
"Cannons are large firearms that can fire heavy projectiles over long "
"distances. They are very strong attackers but equally weak defenders and "
"will need an escort to be effective."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:779 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1199
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1423 data/classic/units.ruleset:1244
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1267 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1344
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1574 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1427
msgid "Artillery"
msgstr "Артилерия"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:805
msgid ""
"The artillery is an upgraded cannon with improved defensive as well as "
"offensive capabilities. It can shoot over city walls, ignoring their effect."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:812 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1265
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1489 data/classic/units.ruleset:1310
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1333 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1410
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1643 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1493
msgid "Fighter"
msgstr "Изтребител"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:839 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1297
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1516 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1520
msgid ""
"Fighters are your first airborne units. They can move anywhere and attack "
"any unit."
msgstr ""
"Изтребителите са първите ви въздушни единици. Могат да се движат навсякъде и "
"да нападат всякакви единици."

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:845 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1303
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1525 data/classic/units.ruleset:1349
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1372 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1449
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1678 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1529
msgid "Bomber"
msgstr "Бомбардировач"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:871 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1329
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1551 data/classic/units.ruleset:1375
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1399 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1475
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1704 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1555
msgid ""
"Bombers are specialized airborne units that may only attack ground targets, "
"not other airborne units."
msgstr ""
"Бомбардировачите са специализирани въздушни единици, които могат да нападат "
"само наземни цели, не други въздушни единици."

#. TRANS: unit type
#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:879 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1443
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1678 data/classic/units.ruleset:1492
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1516 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1591
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1827 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1682
msgid "Trireme"
msgstr "Трирема"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:906
msgid ""
"The Trireme is your first boat unit. It can act as a transport ship and has "
"rudimentary offensive capabilities, but may not stray too far from the shore."
msgstr ""
"Триремата е първата ви морска единица. Може да служи за транспортен кораб и "
"има зачатъчни нападателни способности, но не може да се отдалечава много от "
"брега."

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:913
msgid "Sail"
msgstr "Платноход"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:940
msgid ""
"The Sail replaces the Trireme and is much more reliable on the open seas."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:946 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1546
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1781 data/classic/units.ruleset:1593
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1618 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1692
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2072 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1786
msgid "Frigate"
msgstr "Фрегата"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:973 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1573
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1620 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1645
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1719
msgid ""
"The Frigate is a highly versatile boat unit, that is both a strong offensive "
"unit as well as a decent transport ship."
msgstr ""
"Фрегатата е много гъвкава морска единица, едновременно силна нападателна "
"единица и сносен транспортен кораб."

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:980 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1580
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1813 data/classic/units.ruleset:1627
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1652 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1726
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2140 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1818
msgid "Ironclad"
msgstr "Броненосец"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1006 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1606
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1653 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1678
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1752
msgid ""
"The Ironclad is an armored ship that is much more sturdy than the Frigate "
"but loses the latter's transport capability."
msgstr ""
"Броненосецът е брониран кораб, който е много по-издържлив от Фрегатата, но "
"не може да служи за транспорт като нея."

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1013 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1647
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1884 data/classic/units.ruleset:1694
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1719 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1793
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2211 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1889
msgid "Cruiser"
msgstr "Крайцер"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1039 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1673
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1910 data/classic/units.ruleset:1720
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1745 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1819
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2237 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1915
msgid "The Cruiser is a strong offensive boat unit."
msgstr "Крайцерът е силна нападателна морска единица."

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1044 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1714
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1951 data/classic/units.ruleset:1762
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1787 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1861
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2279 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1957
msgid "Battleship"
msgstr "Линкор"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1070 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1740
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1977 data/classic/units.ruleset:1788
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1813 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1887
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2305 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1987
msgid ""
"The Battleship is the supreme naval unit with excellent offensive and "
"defensive values."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1076 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1746
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:33 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1983
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1794 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1819
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1893 data/royale/units.ruleset:34
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2311 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:33
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1993
msgid "Submarine"
msgstr "Подводница"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1103 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1775
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2012 data/classic/units.ruleset:1823
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1848 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1922
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2339 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2022
msgid ""
"Traveling under the surface of the ocean, Submarines have a very high "
"strategic value, but a weak defense if caught off guard."
msgstr ""
"Плъзгащите се под океанската повърхност Подводници имат много висока "
"стратегическа стойност, но защитата им е слаба ако бъдат изненадани."

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1110 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1782
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2019 data/classic/units.ruleset:1830
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1855 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1929
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2393 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2029
msgid "Carrier"
msgstr "Самолетоносач"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1137 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1809
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2046 data/classic/units.ruleset:1857
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1883 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1956
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2420 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2058
msgid "The Carrier is a mobile airport."
msgstr "Самолетоносачът е подвижно летище."

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1139 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1811
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2052 data/classic/units.ruleset:1859
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1885 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1958
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2426 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2064
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"TIP: Guard Carriers with a handful of fast-moving ships and a battleship, as "
"losing a fully-equipped Carrier is VERY painful and expensive."
msgstr ""
"ИДЕЯ:  Охранявайте Самолетоносачите с по няколко бързоподвижни кораба и един "
"линкор, защото загубата на напълно снаряжен Самолетоносач е МНОГО болезнена "
"и скъпа."

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1146 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1818
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2059 data/classic/units.ruleset:1866
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1892 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1965
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2433 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2071
msgid "Transport"
msgstr "Транспорт"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1173 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1845
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2092 data/classic/units.ruleset:1893
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1919 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1992
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2465 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2104
msgid ""
"The Transport cannot attack on its own but may defend itself when under "
"attack."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1205 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1912
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1966 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1993
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2065 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2240
msgid ""
"You can build Nuclear units when you have the required advance, and the "
"Manhattan Project wonder has been built by any player."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1208 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1915
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"On impact, the blast will destroy any unit in an area 3 tiles wide (3x3 "
"squares for rectangular grids), including friendly units. Any city within "
"the blast area loses half its population, and land tiles within the blast "
"area are subject to nuclear fallout, which appears as pollution and "
"contributes to global warming."
msgstr ""
"При попадение, взривът ще разруши всички единици на поле с ширина 3 плочки "
"(3 на 3 квадратчета за квадратни мрежи), включително и приятелските единици. "
"Всеки град в обсега на взрива ще загуби половината си население, а някои "
"сухоземни плочки на поразената площ ще претърпят радиоактивно заразяване."

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1214
msgid ""
"TIP 1:  Nuking the ocean will not generate fallout, and is a most effective "
"(but expensive!!) way of getting rid of enemy ships."
msgstr ""
"ИДЕЯ 1: Ядрен удар върху океана не разпространява радиоактивност и е най-"
"ефективният (но скъп!!!) начин за отърваване от вражески кораби."

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1218
msgid ""
"TIP 2:  You may be involved in a situation where you have invaded an enemy "
"country en masse, but the enemy cities are too strong. Before using a "
"Nuclear unit, assemble a gang of Settlers next to the city and have them "
"ready to fix the fallout on the same turn it occurs!  This minimizes the "
"chance of global warming. Eco-friendly nukes!"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1228 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1935
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2196 data/classic/units.ruleset:1991
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2018 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2090
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2733 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2268
msgid "Diplomat"
msgstr "Дипломат"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1259 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2237
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2030 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2057
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2129 data/royale/units.ruleset:2773
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2309
msgid ""
"A Diplomat is an official that carries your dispatches and is authorized to "
"deal with foreign dignitaries. He may also undertake various covert "
"operations with the intent of harming your opponents. Diplomats in your own "
"cities defend them against such actions."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1265 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1972
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2036 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2063
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2135
msgid ""
"Many covert actions may be attempted even in peacetime, but the more "
"aggressive actions will be discovered and cause diplomatic incidents, which "
"can allow Republics and Democracies to break treaties."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1269 data/classic/units.ruleset:2040
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2067 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2139
msgid ""
"If a foreign unit is alone on a tile, you may attempt to bribe it with your "
"Diplomat. By paying a sum of gold the unit will immediately become yours. "
"The exact sum depends on the status of the unit and that of the civilization "
"owning it. However, units belonging to Democratic governments cannot be "
"bribed. Bribery when not at war will cause a diplomatic incident."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1276 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1983
msgid ""
"Diplomats can also perform a number of actions in another player's city, "
"although each Diplomat may attempt only one action. Most of these actions "
"have a chance of failure. Also, any enemy Diplomats or Spies in the city "
"will oppose hostile actions. In this case, either your unit or the defending "
"unit will die. If the defending unit dies, you lose one movement point and "
"may try again."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1283 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1990
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2264 data/classic/units.ruleset:2055
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2082 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2154
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2800 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2336
msgid "The actions available to Diplomats in a city are:"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1285 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1992
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2057 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2084
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2156 data/royale/units.ruleset:2802
msgid ""
" - \"Establish Embassy\": This action always succeeds, and gives permanent "
"contact with the city's owner, as well as intelligence on their national "
"budget and technology."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1289 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1996
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2272 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2499
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2061 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2088
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2160 data/royale/units.ruleset:2806
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2344 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2575
msgid ""
" - \"Investigate City\": Your unit attempts to report detailed information "
"about the city: its status, what buildings and units are within, and what it "
"is currently producing."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1293 data/civ2/units.ruleset:2000
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2276 data/classic/units.ruleset:2065
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2092 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2164
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2810 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2348
msgid ""
" - \"Sabotage City\": Your unit attempts either to disrupt all the city's "
"work so far towards its current project, or to destroy an existing building "
"in the city, at random. Once built, Palaces and Wonders cannot be sabotaged, "
"and attempts to sabotage City Walls or any building in a capital each halve "
"the chance of success. Sabotage may only be attempted when openly at war."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1300 data/civ2/units.ruleset:2007
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2283 data/classic/units.ruleset:2072
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2099 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2171
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2355
msgid ""
" - \"Steal Technology\": Your unit attempts to learn the secrets of a random "
"technology known to the city's owner but not to you. Technology may only be "
"stolen once from a given enemy city by Diplomats. This action may be "
"attempted even when not at war, but will cause a diplomatic incident."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1306 data/civ2/units.ruleset:2013
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2078 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2105
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2177
msgid ""
" - \"Incite a Revolt\": In return for gold a foreign city will change "
"allegiance and join your empire, bringing along all nearby units that call "
"it home, but reducing its size by 1. Units in other cities remain in the "
"enemy's control, but units outside cities are lost to both players. The "
"exact sum depends on the status of the city and that of the civilization "
"that owns it. It is not possible to incite a rebellion in a capital, or in "
"any city governed by a democracy. Incitement may be attempted in peacetime, "
"but will cause a diplomatic incident."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1316 data/classic/units.ruleset:2088
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2115 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2187
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2827 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2371
msgid ""
"In some game strategies, hordes of Diplomats can be used to wreak havoc on "
"the enemy. Little wonder that Diplomats are often viewed with suspicion and "
"fear!"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1323 data/civ2/units.ruleset:2090
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2380 data/classic/units.ruleset:2168
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2195 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2267
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3101 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2455
msgid "Caravan"
msgstr "Керван"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1349 data/civ2/units.ruleset:2116
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2194 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2221
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A Caravan carries goods or material for trading with distant cities and "
"foreign countries, or to help build wonders in your cities."
msgstr ""
"Керваните носят стока или материали за търговия с далечни градове и чужди "
"страни, или в помощ на строежа на чудеса в градовете ви."

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1352
msgid ""
"Caravans can establish trade routes with your own cities or those of other "
"nations (even enemies) by traveling to them. A route's ongoing revenue is "
"doubled if the two cities involved are on different continents, and doubled "
"again if the cities are from different civilizations. This last condition "
"means the net benefit to your civilization of a trade route is the same "
"regardless of whether you own both cities or only one of them. If you only "
"own one city, trade in each city is doubled, but you only get the benefit "
"from one end of the route. Each city can support a maximum of three trade "
"routes."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1362 data/civ2/units.ruleset:2129
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2210 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2237
msgid ""
"Every Caravan that is used to build a wonder will add 50 shields towards the "
"production of the wonder."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1365 data/civ2/units.ruleset:2132
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2421 data/classic/units.ruleset:2213
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2240 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2299
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3139 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2497
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"TIP: You can stockpile a stack of Caravans in advance and bring them all "
"into a city where you have started to build a wonder, and finish it in only "
"one turn!"
msgstr ""
"ИДЕЯ:  Можете да натрупате много Кервани предварително и да изпратите всички "
"в град, където сте започнали да строите чудо, и да го завършите само за един "
"ход!"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1372 data/civ2/units.ruleset:2202
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2547 data/classic/units.ruleset:2324
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2356 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2411
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3270 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2623
msgid "Barbarian Leader"
msgstr "Варварски лидер"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1398 data/civ2/units.ruleset:2228
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2580 data/classic/units.ruleset:2357
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2389 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2444
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3303 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2656
msgid ""
"One Barbarian Leader appears every time there is a barbarian uprising "
"somewhere in the world."
msgstr ""
"Един Варварски водач се появява всеки път щом някъде по света има варварско "
"въстание."

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1401
msgid ""
"When a Barbarian Leader is killed on a tile without any defending units, the "
"100 gold ransom is paid, but only to land units."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:65 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:65
#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:65 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:67
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:64 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:65
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:65
msgid "Airport"
msgstr "Летище"

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:81
msgid ""
"Allows a city to produce veteran air units (including helicopters) and "
"missiles. Also, damaged air units (including helicopters) which stay in town "
"for one full turn without moving are completely restored."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:86 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:88
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:85
msgid ""
"Two cities with Airports can airlift one unit per turn. Airlifting instantly "
"transports the unit from one city to another and will use all of the unit's "
"movement points. A unit must have some movement points left to be airlifted."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:110 data/classic/buildings.ruleset:110
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:136
msgid ""
"Allows a city to grow larger than size 8. A Sewer System is also required "
"for a city to grow larger than size 12."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:158 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:238
#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:162 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:167
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:188 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:238
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With a Barracks, each new land unit built in a city will automatically have "
"Veteran status, which means that its attack and defense strengths are "
"increased by 50%."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:162 data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:190
#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:217 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:242
#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:271 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:298
#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:166 data/classic/buildings.ruleset:195
#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:222 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:171
#: data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:200
#: data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:227
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:192
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:221
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:248 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:273
#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:303 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:331
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:242 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:270
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:296
msgid ""
"Also, damaged land units which stay in town for one full turn without moving "
"are completely restored."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:186 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:267
#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:191 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:196
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:217 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:266
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With a Barracks II, each new land unit built in a city will automatically "
"have Veteran status, which means that its attack and defense strengths are "
"increased by 50%."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:213 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:294
#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:218 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:223
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:244 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:292
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With a Barracks III, each new land unit built in a city will automatically "
"have Veteran status, which means that its attack and defense strengths are "
"increased by 50%."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:239 data/classic/buildings.ruleset:245
#: data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:250
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:271
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A Cathedral makes 3 unhappy citizens content in a city, making it easier to "
"maintain order in that city. However, it does not affect citizens made "
"unhappy by military activity. The discovery of Theology increases the effect "
"of a Cathedral, making an additional unhappy citizen content. The discovery "
"of Communism lessens the effect of a Cathedral, reducing by one the number "
"of unhappy citizens made content."
msgstr ""
"Катедралата прави 4 нещастни жители доволни в даден град, правейки по-лесно "
"поддържането на реда в него; при все това, тя не влияе на жителите които са "
"недоволни от военна дейност."

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:267 data/classic/buildings.ruleset:273
#: data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:278
msgid ""
"City Walls make it easier to defend a city. They triple the defense strength "
"of units within the city against land and helicopter units. They are "
"ineffective against airborne and sea units as well as Howitzers. City Walls "
"also prevent the loss of population which occurs when a defending unit is "
"destroyed by a land unit."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:276 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:358
#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:282 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:287
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:308 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:391
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:355
msgid "Coastal Defense"
msgstr "Брегова отбрана"

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:293 data/classic/buildings.ruleset:299
#: data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:304
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:325
msgid ""
"Increases the defense strength of units within a city by a factor of 2 when "
"defending against bombardments from enemy ships."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:315
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Entertains the citizens of a city, making 3 unhappy citizens content (four "
"after the discovery of Electronics). However, it does not affect citizens "
"made unhappy by military activity."
msgstr ""
"Катедралата прави 4 нещастни жители доволни в даден град, правейки по-лесно "
"поддържането на реда в него; при все това, тя не влияе на жителите които са "
"недоволни от военна дейност."

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:339
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Reduces the corruption and waste in a city by 50%, and makes the revolt cost "
"of the city 4 times bigger. These effects are redundant in your capital city."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:343
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Under a Democracy, a Courthouse also makes 1 unhappy citizen content, unless "
"that citizen is unhappy about military activity."
msgstr ""
"Катедралата прави 4 нещастни жители доволни в даден град, правейки по-лесно "
"поддържането на реда в него; при все това, тя не влияе на жителите които са "
"недоволни от военна дейност."

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:398 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:494
#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:406 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:413
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:404 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:526
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:489
msgid "Harbor"
msgstr "Пристан"

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:416 data/classic/buildings.ruleset:424
#: data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:431
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:422
msgid ""
"Gives one extra food resource on all Oceanic tiles. The city needs to be "
"coastal to build this improvement."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:448
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A city can only have one Power Plant, Hydro Plant, Nuclear Plant, or Solar "
"Plant.  A city can only build a Hydro Plant if it is next to (or on) a River "
"tile."
msgstr ""
"В даден град може да има само една ВЕЦ, ТЕЦ или АЕЦ. В града може да се "
"построи ВЕЦ само ако той се намира до (или на) Планина или Река."

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:517 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:585
msgid ""
"Neutralizes the pollution generated by the population. The population simply "
"has no effect on the pollution generated in the city."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:542 data/classic/buildings.ruleset:553
#: data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:613
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:548
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Together with a Factory, a Manufacturing Plant increases the shield "
"production in a city by 100%. A Manufacturing Plant on its own increases "
"shield production by 50%."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:567
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Reduces the amount of pollution generated by production in a city by 50%. It "
"also increases the shield production of a Factory or Mfg. Plant in the city. "
"A Factory and a Nuclear Plant together give a 100% production bonus, and a "
"Factory, Mfg. Plant and Nuclear Plant together give a 150% production bonus."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:574 data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:720
#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:871
msgid ""
"A city can only have one Power Plant, Hydro Plant, Nuclear Plant, or Solar "
"Plant."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:583 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:704
#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:605 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:662
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:589 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:738
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:694
msgid "Offshore Platform"
msgstr "Морска платформа"

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:600 data/classic/buildings.ruleset:622
#: data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:679
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:606
msgid ""
"Adds 1 extra shield resource on all Oceanic tiles worked by a city. The city "
"needs to be coastal to build this improvement."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:623 data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:629
msgid ""
"Makes a city the capital and the center of your government. Corruption and "
"waste in other cities is related to how far away from the capital they are, "
"except when the government is Democracy or Communism. On top of this, "
"corruption and waste in your capital itself is half of what it would "
"otherwise be (as if it had a Courthouse)."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:630 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:751
msgid ""
"The cost to enemy Diplomats and Spies of inciting a revolt in a city also "
"depends upon the city's distance from the capital, under all forms of "
"government. Your capital city itself cannot be incited to revolt, and enjoys "
"a bonus when enemy agents try to evade your own agents stationed in the "
"city, or sabotage your buildings."
msgstr ""

