msgstr ""
"Партизаните са нередовни бойци които умеят добре да се възползват от терена."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:699
msgid ""
"A number of Partisans are granted free when an enemy conquers your city -- "
"they automatically assume defensive positions in the surrounding countryside "
"-- but only under these conditions:\n"
" - Guerilla Warfare must be known by at least one player.\n"
" - You must be the player who originally built the city.\n"
" - You must know about Communism and Gunpowder.\n"
" - You must run either a Democracy or a Communist government."
msgstr ""
"Получавате безплатно известен брой Партизани когато ваш град бъде завладян "
"-- те автоматично заемат защитни позиции в околностите му -- но само при "
"следните условия:\n"
" - Технологията Партизанска война трябва да е известна поне на един играч.\n"
" - Градът трябва да е бил основан от вас.\n"
" - Трябва да са ви известни Комунизъм и Барут.\n"
" - Трябва да имате Демократично или Комунистическо управление."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:710 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:868
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:819 data/experimental/units.ruleset:841
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:855 data/royale/units.ruleset:1009
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:872
msgid "Alpine Troops"
msgstr "Алпийски части"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:736 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:896
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:845 data/experimental/units.ruleset:867
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:881 data/royale/units.ruleset:1037
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:900
msgid "Alpine Troops are highly mobile units as well as excellent defenders."
msgstr ""
"Алписките части са не само изключително подвижни единици, но и отлични "
"защитници."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:800 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1010
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:909 data/experimental/units.ruleset:931
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:945 data/royale/units.ruleset:1151
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1014
msgid "Marines are infantry who are experts at marine warfare."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:831 data/classic/units.ruleset:940
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:976
msgid ""
"Paratroopers are experts at airborne attacks. From a friendly city or "
"airbase, Paratroopers who have not expended any movement points can paradrop "
"directly to any tile in range, and be immediately ready to act there. "
"(Beware dropping into unseen territory, as Paratroopers landing on a tile "
"occupied by enemy units are easy targets!)"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:868 data/classic/units.ruleset:977
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1000 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1013
msgid ""
"The Mechanized Infantry has the strongest defensive strength of any land "
"unit, but is only available near the end of the technology tree."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:875 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1089
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:984 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1007
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1020 data/royale/units.ruleset:1232
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1093
msgid "Horsemen"
msgstr "Конници"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:901 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1115
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1010 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1033
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1046 data/royale/units.ruleset:1258
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1119
msgid ""
"Horsemen are mounted warriors and an early shock-troop that can penetrate "
"deep into enemy territory."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:934 data/classic/units.ruleset:1043
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1066 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1079
msgid ""
"Chariots are horse-pulled war wagons, stronger but more expensive than "
"horsemen."
msgstr ""
"Колесниците са теглени от коне бойни коли, по-силни от конниците, но и по-"
"скъпи."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:940 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1158
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1085 data/royale/units.ruleset:1301
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1162
msgid "Elephants"
msgstr "Слонове"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:966 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1111
msgid ""
"Elephants are towering animals trained for war that are often used as "
"powerful shock troops, but defend poorly against most other units."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:972 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1190
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1117 data/royale/units.ruleset:1333
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1194
msgid "Crusaders"
msgstr "Кръстоносци"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:998 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1216
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1220
msgid ""
"Crusaders are highly disciplined mounted warriors driven by a higher cause."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1036 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1254
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1081 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1104
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1181 data/royale/units.ruleset:1400
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1258
msgid "Dragoons"
msgstr "Драгуни"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1063 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1280
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1108 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1131
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1208 data/royale/units.ruleset:1426
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1284
msgid "Dragoons are mounted warriors carrying early firearms."
msgstr "Драгуните са конници въоръжени с ранни огнестрелни оръжия."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1094 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1311
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1139 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1162
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1239 data/royale/units.ruleset:1457
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1315
msgid "Cavalry are mounted and highly trained soldiers."
msgstr "Кавалеристите са добре тренирани войници на коне."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1225 data/classic/units.ruleset:1270
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1293 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1370
msgid ""
"The artillery is an upgraded cannon. It is a very strong attacker but "
"equally weak defender and will need an escort to be effective."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1232 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1456
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1277 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1300
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1377 data/royale/units.ruleset:1609
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1460
msgid "Howitzer"
msgstr "Гаубица"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1258 data/classic/units.ruleset:1303
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1326 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1403
msgid ""
"Howitzers are upgraded artillery with improved defensive as well as "
"offensive capabilities. They can shoot over city walls, ignoring their "
"effect."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1363 data/classic/units.ruleset:1409
msgid ""
"The Helicopter is a very powerful unit, as it can both fly and conquer "
"cities. Care must be exercised, because Helicopters lose a small amount of "
"health for every turn not spent in a city or airbase or on a Carrier, unless "
"you have the United Nations wonder, and Helicopters may be attacked by "
"ground units."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1372 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1610
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1418 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1442
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1517 data/royale/units.ruleset:1759
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1614
msgid "Stealth Fighter"
msgstr "Стелт-изтребител"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1404 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1638
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1787 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1642
msgid "An improved Fighter, with improved attack and a higher movement radius."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1410 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1644
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1457 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1481
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1556 data/royale/units.ruleset:1793
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1648
msgid "Stealth Bomber"
msgstr "Стелт-бомбардировач"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1436 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1671
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1485 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1509
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1584 data/royale/units.ruleset:1820
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1675
msgid "An improved Bomber, with improved attack and a higher movement radius."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1470
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The Trireme is your first boat unit. It can act as a transport ship and has "
"rudimentary offensive capabilities. If it ends its turn away from shore, it "
"has a 1/2 chance of sinking. This is reduced to 1/3 after Seafaring, 1/4 "
"after Navigation, and eliminated by the Lighthouse wonder."
msgstr ""
"Триремата е първата ви морска единица. Може да служи за транспортен кораб и "
"има зачатъчни нападателни способности, но не може да се отдалечава много от "
"брега."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1479 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1713
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1526 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1551
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1625 data/royale/units.ruleset:2004
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1717
msgid "Caravel"
msgstr "Каравела"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1506
msgid ""
"The Caravel replaces the Trireme and is much more reliable on the open seas."
msgstr "Каравелата заменя Триремата и е много по-надеждна в открито море."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1512 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1747
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1559 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1584
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1658 data/royale/units.ruleset:2038
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1752
msgid "Galleon"
msgstr "Галеон"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1539 data/classic/units.ruleset:1586
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1611 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1685
msgid ""
"The Galleon is a pure transport ship and cannot attack other ships, though "
"it may still defend itself when attacked."
msgstr ""
"Галеонът е чисто транспортен кораб и не може да напада други кораби, но все "
"пак може да се защитава когато бъде нападнат."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1613 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1845
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1660 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1685
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1759 data/royale/units.ruleset:2172
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1850
msgid "Destroyer"
msgstr "Разрушител"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1639 data/classic/units.ruleset:1686
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1711 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1785
msgid "An improved Ironclad, with better move rate and vision."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1641 data/classic/units.ruleset:1688
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1713 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1787
msgid ""
"TIP: A very fast unit, which is very useful for hunting down enemy "
"Transports."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1678 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1915
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1725 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1750
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1824 data/royale/units.ruleset:2242
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1920
msgid "AEGIS Cruiser"
msgstr "Крайцер „Егида“"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1708 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1945
msgid ""
"The AEGIS Cruiser is equipped with an advanced defensive missile system."
msgstr ""
"Ракетният крайцер е въоръжен с усъвършенствана защитна ракетна система "
"„Егида“ (AEGIS)."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1851 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2102
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1899 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1925
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1998 data/royale/units.ruleset:2523
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2114
msgid "Cruise Missile"
msgstr "Крилата ракета"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1877 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2129
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1925 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1952
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2024 data/royale/units.ruleset:2550
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2141
msgid ""
"The Cruise Missile is a long-distance missile that can strike deep into "
"enemy territory."
msgstr ""
"Крилатата ракета може да нанася удари дълбоко във вражеската територия."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1880 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2132
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1928 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1955
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2027 data/royale/units.ruleset:2553
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2144
msgid ""
"TIP: A handful of these can successfully keep the waters around your "
"treasured homeland free of enemy ships."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1921 data/classic/units.ruleset:1977
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2004 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2076
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"TIP 1: Nuking the ocean will not generate fallout, and is a most effective "
"(but expensive!!) way of getting rid of enemy ships."
msgstr ""
"ИДЕЯ 1: Ядрен удар върху океана не разпространява радиоактивност и е най-"
"ефективният (но скъп!!!) начин за отърваване от вражески кораби."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1925
msgid ""
"TIP 2: You may be involved in a situation where you've invaded an enemy "
"country en masse, but the enemy cities are too strong. Before using a "
"Nuclear unit, assemble a gang of Settlers and/or Engineers next to the city "
"and have them ready to fix the fallout on the same turn it occurs!  This "
"minimizes the chance of global warming. Eco-friendly nukes!"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1966
msgid ""
"A Diplomat is an official that carries your dispatches and is authorized to "
"deal with foreign dignitaries. He may also undertake various covert "
"operations with the intent of harming your opponents; Diplomats in your own "
"cities defend them against such actions."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1976
msgid ""
"If a foreign unit is alone on a tile, you may attempt to bribe it with your "
"Diplomat. By paying a sum of gold the unit will immediately become yours; "
"the exact sum depends on the status of the unit and that of the civilization "
"owning it. However, units belonging to Democratic governments cannot be "
"bribed. Bribery when not at war will cause a diplomatic incident."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2023 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2299
msgid ""
"In some game strategies, hordes of Diplomats can be used to wreak havoc on "
"the enemy.  Little wonder that Diplomats are often viewed with suspicion and "
"fear!"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2030 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2309
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2098 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2125
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2197 data/royale/units.ruleset:2837
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2381
msgid "Spy"
msgstr "Шпионин"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2061 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2350
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2138 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2165
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2237 data/royale/units.ruleset:2877
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2422
msgid ""
"A Spy is more skilled in the arts of espionage than her Diplomat predecessor."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2063 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2352
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2140 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2239
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2424
msgid ""
"She can perform all the functions of the Diplomat. Refer to the Diplomat "
"entry for more details. Unlike a Diplomat, a Spy may also survive an "
"operation in a foreign city and become more experienced as a result. Spies "
"are also more effective than Diplomats at defending cities against foreign "
"Diplomats and Spies."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2069 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2245
msgid ""
"A Spy can also be used to:\n"
"\n"
" - sabotage an enemy unit (reducing its hit points to half), if it is alone "
"on a tile and the players are at war;\n"
" - poison the water supply of an enemy city (reducing the population by "
"one);\n"
" - steal specific technology (with a reduced chance of success);\n"
" - steal further technologies from a city which has already been stolen from "
"(although cities become more resistant each time they are stolen from);\n"
" - sabotage predetermined city targets (with a reduced chance of success)."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2081 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2370
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2158 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2185
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2257 data/royale/units.ruleset:2893
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2445
msgid ""
"A Spy that survives the more aggressive actions (sabotage, theft, inciting "
"rebellion, and poisoning) escapes to the safety of the nearest friendly city."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2085
msgid "Spies built under a Communist government will be built as veteran."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2119
msgid ""
"Caravans can establish trade routes with your own cities or those of other "
"nations (even enemies) by traveling to them. A route's ongoing revenue is "
"doubled if the two cities involved are on different continents, and doubled "
"again if the cities are from different civilizations. This last condition "
"means the net benefit to your civilization of a trade route is the same "
"regardless of whether you own both cities or only one of them; if you only "
"own one city, trade in each city is doubled, but you only get the benefit "
"from one end of the route. Each city can support a maximum of three trade "
"routes."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2139 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2428
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2220 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2247
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2306 data/royale/units.ruleset:3146
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2504
msgid "Freight"
msgstr "Камион"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2165 data/classic/units.ruleset:2246
msgid "The Freight unit replaces the Caravan, and moves at twice the speed."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2170 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2460
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2251 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2279
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2338 data/royale/units.ruleset:3178
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2536
msgid "Explorer"
msgstr "Откривател"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2196 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2486
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2277 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2305
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2364 data/royale/units.ruleset:3204
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2562
msgid ""
"Explorers are brave individuals that are very useful for mapping unknown "
"territory."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2231 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2583
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2360 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2392
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2447 data/royale/units.ruleset:3306
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2659
msgid ""
"When a Barbarian Leader is killed on a tile without any defending units, the "
"100 gold ransom is paid, but only to land units and helicopters."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:81 data/classic/buildings.ruleset:81
#: data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:83 data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:80
#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:82 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:81
msgid ""
"Allows a city to produce veteran air units (including helicopters and "
"missiles). Also, damaged air units (again, including helicopters) which stay "
"in town for one full turn without moving are completely restored."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:86
msgid ""
"Two cities with Airports can airlift one unit per turn, including aircraft. "
"Airlifting instantly transports the unit from one city to another and will "
"use all of the unit's movement points. A unit must have some movement points "
"left to be airlifted, and cannot carry cargo."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:113 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:145
#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:178 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:116
#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:150 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:185
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:115 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:147
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:180
msgid ""
"Allows a city to grow larger than size 8. A Sewer System is required for a "
"city to grow larger than size 16."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:116 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:148
#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:181 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:119
#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:153 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:188
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:118 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:150
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:183
msgid ""
"These larger cities enjoy increased defense (+50%) against both land and sea "
"units. However, such large settlements have a small risk of fire, which can "
"destroy buildings in the city."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:120 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:123
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:122
msgid ""
"Starting at size 5, growing cities incur an increasing risk of plague due to "
"overcrowding. An Aqueduct reduces that base chance by 30%."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:123 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:126
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:125
msgid ""
"Building an Aqueduct in a city without access to a lake or river requires "
"knowledge of Construction, and it costs more to build and maintain."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:129 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:132
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:131
#, fuzzy
msgid "Aqueduct, Lake"
msgstr "Акведукт"

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:152 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:157
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:154
msgid ""
"Starting at size 5, growing cities incur an increasing risk of plague due to "
"overcrowding. An Aqueduct, Lake reduces that base chance by 30%."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:155 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:160
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:157
msgid ""
"Aqueducts in cities with access to a lake require no special technology and "
"are cheap to build and maintain."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:161 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:166
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:163
#, fuzzy
msgid "Aqueduct, River"
msgstr "Акведукт"

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:185 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:192
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:187
msgid ""
"Starting at size 5, growing cities incur an increasing risk of plague due to "
"overcrowding. An Aqueduct, River reduces that base chance by 30%."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:188 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:195
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:190
msgid ""
"Aqueducts in cities with access to a river require no special technology and "
"are cheap to build and maintain."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:212
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
